727405f-a.title: Queens: Metropolitan Avenue - 65th Place
727405f-a.text:
Metropolitan Avenue, south side, at 65th Place (houses thereon),
showing in the foreground the J.W. Faber house of 1873. According
to J. Riker Junior's map of Newtown (1852) this hose then was not
in existence. The 2 story building adjoining the peaked roof house
was also erected by him. Adjoining it is a Cemetery stone yard and
office that do not apnear in the 1927 Queens Atlas. The two story
brick building in the baclkground is at 6520 Metropolitan Avenue.
February 1924.
Eucene L. Armbruster Collection
